art for art’s sake” and pursuing broader social and economic aims through the arts, as well as the inherent political conflicts between serving the needs of the artistic community and the needs of Canadian society, between leadership and followership, between autonomy and collaboration, and between emerging and established artistic practices. Combining lively storytelling with insightful analysis, and beautifully produced with dozens of photos of the art, people, and events that have shaped the organization through the years, The Roots of Culture, the Power of Art is essential reading for those with an interest in Canadian arts and culture and cultural policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArt and societyxHistoryxCanadaxCanada. 0aArt and societyzCanadaxHistory. 0aArt and statexHistoryxCanada. 0aArt and statezCanadaxHistory. 0aFederal aid to the artsxHistoryxCanada. 0aFederal aid to the artszCanadaxHistory. 7aART / Canadian.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780773552685?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773552685423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773552685/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles